Doctors and Availability
GET /api/doctors
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>
Returns only active doctors with completed profiles.

GET /api/doctors/available?start=2026-03-09T15:30:00.000Z&durationMinutes=30
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>
Checks doctor profile time window + booking conflicts.

GET /api/doctors/me
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>
(doctor only)

PUT /api/doctors/profile
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>
(doctor only)
{
  "fullName": "Dr. Rahul Sharma",
  "specialization": "Cardiologist",
  "experienceYears": 8,
  "consultationFee": 1200,
  "availableStart": "10:00",
  "availableEnd": "14:00",
  "clinicName": "City Heart Clinic"
}
Required for doctor onboarding completion:
1) fullName
2) specialization
3) experienceYears
4) consultationFee
5) availableStart + availableEnd
6) clinicName is optional

Appointments and Prioritization
POST /api/appointments/book
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>
(patient only)
{
  "doctorId": "<doctor_id>",
  "slotStart": "2026-03-10T11:00:00.000Z",
  "durationMinutes": 30,
  "reason": "",
  "triageReportId": "<optional_triage_report_id>"
}
If reason is empty and triageReportId is provided, selected triage summary is used as appointment reason.

GET /api/appointments/my
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>
(patient only)

GET /api/appointments/doctor
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>
(doctor only)

GET /api/appointments/queue
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>
(doctor/admin only)
Sorted by priorityScore desc, then earliest slot.

PATCH /api/appointments/:appointmentId/status
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>
(doctor/admin only)
{
  "status": "confirmed"
}

Environment
Create server/.env from .env.example.
Leave AI_API_KEY empty for now if needed.
